column25: There are serious lack of psychotherapy training in psychiatry curriculum. Although there are 4 months for it but it's like drop in the sea. We are only introduce with some basic statements about psychodynamic psychotherapy. If we want to learn psychotherapy we must to do it outside residency and pay for it by ourselves. I think that psychotherapy is extremely important in my clinical work in order to better understand and help patients.
column32: Mostly psychodynamic, maybe a bit CBT.
column38: I have supervision once per month.
column69: I hope step by step we will improve psychotherapy learning situation in Europe!

column25: Psychiatry and psychotherapy are quite close. There are many situations when psychoterapeutic knowledge and practice is very important for a psychiatrist.
column32: I cannot say precisely, because I don't know what psychotherapists work in my hospital.

column9: I have recently finished training (within last 5 years)

column25: Psychotherapy helps to understand your patient much better: why this patient has these symptoms at this moment. It's not about reducing symptoms only, it's about teaching the patient new way (thinking or behaving) to cope the problems  himself. Sharing information with patient helps him understand himself better, and be more attentive to himself
